# shadcn/ui Rules

## Setup
```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest init
# When prompted:
# - Style: Default
# - Base color: Neutral
# - CSS variables: Yes
```

## Install These Components Upfront
Run all of these before building any UI:
```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest add button
npx shadcn-ui@latest add card
npx shadcn-ui@latest add dialog
npx shadcn-ui@latest add input
npx shadcn-ui@latest add textarea
npx shadcn-ui@latest add select
npx shadcn-ui@latest add slider
npx shadcn-ui@latest add table
npx shadcn-ui@latest add tabs
npx shadcn-ui@latest add badge
npx shadcn-ui@latest add label
npx shadcn-ui@latest add separator
npx shadcn-ui@latest add avatar
npx shadcn-ui@latest add dropdown-menu
npx shadcn-ui@latest add toast
npx shadcn-ui@latest add progress
npx shadcn-ui@latest add switch
npx shadcn-ui@latest add skeleton
npx shadcn-ui@latest add alert
npx shadcn-ui@latest add sheet
```

## Critical Rules
- NEVER build a custom input, button, dialog, or select from scratch — always use shadcn first
- ALWAYS import shadcn components from `@/components/ui/` — never from the package directly
- NEVER modify files inside `components/ui/` — those are auto-generated, treat them as read-only
- If you need to extend a shadcn component, wrap it in a new component in `components/shared/` or the relevant feature folder
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional className merging on shadcn components

## Customization Pattern
Override shadcn defaults using Tailwind classes on the component, not by editing the source:
```tsx
// WRONG — editing components/ui/button.tsx directly
// RIGHT — override at usage site
<Button className="bg-pink-400 hover:bg-pink-500 text-white w-full">
  Submit
</Button>
```

## Component Usage Patterns for This App

### Dialog (used for Event Wizard, Add Category, Invite Judge)
```tsx
import {
  Dialog,
  DialogContent,
  DialogHeader,
  DialogTitle,
  DialogTrigger,
} from "@/components/ui/dialog"

<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger asChild>
    <Button>Create Event</Button>
  </DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent className="max-w-2xl">
    <DialogHeader>
      <DialogTitle>Create New Event</DialogTitle>
    </DialogHeader>
    {/* wizard steps here */}
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

### Slider (used for scoring criteria)
```tsx
import { Slider } from "@/components/ui/slider"

<Slider
  min={0}
  max={criterion.maxScore}
  step={1}
  value={[value]}
  onValueChange={([v]) => setValue(v)}
  className="accent-pink-400"
/>
```

### Switch (used for settings toggles)
```tsx
import { Switch } from "@/components/ui/switch"
import { Label } from "@/components/ui/label"

<div className="flex items-center gap-3">
  <Switch
    id="anonymous-mode"
    checked={anonymousMode}
    onCheckedChange={setAnonymousMode}
  />
  <Label htmlFor="anonymous-mode">Anonymous Judging</Label>
</div>
```

### Toast (used for success/error feedback)
```tsx
// In layout.tsx
import { Toaster } from "@/components/ui/toast"
<Toaster />

// In any component
import { useToast } from "@/components/ui/use-toast"
const { toast } = useToast()

toast({
  title: "Score submitted",
  description: "Your evaluation has been locked.",
})

// For errors
toast({
  title: "Something went wrong",
  description: error.message,
  variant: "destructive",
})
```

### Skeleton (used for all loading states)
```tsx
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton"

// Card loading state
<div className="bg-white rounded-md border border-gray-200 flex flex-col">
  <Skeleton className="aspect-square rounded-t-md rounded-b-none" />
  <div className="p-4 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <Skeleton className="h-5 w-3/4" />
    <Skeleton className="h-4 w-1/2" />
    <Skeleton className="h-6 w-20" />
  </div>
</div>
```

### Badge (used for category tags and status pills)
```tsx
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge"

// Override with pink accent for category
<Badge className="bg-pink-400 text-white border-none">
  {category}
</Badge>

// Status variants
<Badge variant="outline" className="text-green-600 border-green-600">Scored</Badge>
<Badge variant="outline" className="text-yellow-600 border-yellow-600">Pending</Badge>
```

### Progress (used for judge progress bars)
```tsx
import { Progress } from "@/components/ui/progress"

<Progress
  value={Math.round((scored / assigned) * 100)}
  className="h-2 bg-gray-100 [&>div]:bg-pink-400"
/>
```

### Sheet (used for mobile sidebar)
```tsx
import { Sheet, SheetContent, SheetTrigger } from "@/components/ui/sheet"

// Mobile nav drawer
<Sheet>
  <SheetTrigger asChild>
    <Button variant="ghost" size="icon" className="lg:hidden">
      <MenuIcon className="size-5" />
    </Button>
  </SheetTrigger>
  <SheetContent side="left" className="w-64 p-0">
    {/* sidebar content */}
  </SheetContent>
</Sheet>
```

## tailwind.config.ts — Required for shadcn
Make sure `content` includes all paths shadcn needs:
```ts
content: [
  "./pages/**/*.{ts,tsx}",
  "./components/**/*.{ts,tsx}",
  "./app/**/*.{ts,tsx}",
  "./src/**/*.{ts,tsx}",
],
```

## globals.css — shadcn CSS variables
After init, `globals.css` will have `:root` CSS variables for colors.
Override the primary color to match pink accent:
```css
:root {
  --primary: 340 82% 62%;        /* pink-400 equivalent */
  --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
}
```
